{
  "text": "Cell culture. HC-11 cells were maintained in RPMI containing 10% FBS (Invitrogen), 1% penicillin-streptomycin, 5 \u03bcg/ml insulin (Sigma-Aldrich, St. Louis, MO) and 10 ng/ml epidermal growth factor (EGF) (Invitrogen). HC-11 cells stably expressing the iFGFR construct (HC-11/R1) were generated as previously described [CITATION_1] and were acquired from Dr. Jeffrey Rosen. HC-11/R1 cells were maintained in HC-11 medium with the addition of 0.7 \u03bcg/ml puromycin (SigmaAldrich). We received SUM225 and MCF10DCIS.com from Dr. Fariba Behbod (University of Kansas City Medical Center, Kansas City, KS, USA) and maintained as described [CITATION_2] . Table 1 .",
  "correct_citation": {
